---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="For Restaurants & Inns"
  description="Avorix for restaurants and inns: secure your recipes, train your team, bridge staff gaps. Cook app, training, and staff from one source."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="pt-28 pb-16 px-6 bg-gradient-to-b from-brand-50/50 to-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-sm font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-brand-500 mb-4">For Restaurants & Inns</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-neutral-900 leading-tight mb-6">
        Your Inn Stands and Falls With One Person. It Doesn't Have to.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Avorix secures your house recipes, trains your team, and bridges staff gaps with real chefs. So your kitchen holds your standard. Every day. <strong class="text-neutral-900">Even without trained chefs.</strong>
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mb-6">
        <a href="/en/contact" data-cta-location="restaurants-hero" class="bg-brand-500 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-xl font-bold hover:bg-brand-600 transition-colors inline-block">Book a Demo</a>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 text-sm">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-neutral-50 border border-brand-200 text-neutral-800 rounded-full px-4 py-2 font-semibold">&#10003; Official Staff Leasing Permit</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Problem -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-8">When the Chef Leaves, Everything Is at Stake.</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">The resignation isn't a staffing matter. It's an existential question.</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">With the chef go the recipes, the processes, the quality. What remains is a team that improvises — and guests who notice.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Your regulars notice first.</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">First the taste changes, then the reviews come, then the tables stay empty. What took years to build is lost in weeks.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Nobody responds to your job posting.</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">The market is empty. And if someone does respond, they're gone again after one season. The cycle starts over.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mt-6">The question isn't whether it will hit you. The question is how long things will keep going well.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- System -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-neutral-50 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">The Avorix System: Secure Recipes, Train Teams, Bridge Gaps.</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 max-w-3xl mb-8">Think of a sat-nav. A sat-nav gets any driver to the destination, even if they don't know the route. Avorix does the same in your kitchen: it guides any kitchen worker to the finished dish, even if they've never cooked it before.</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">1 &middot; The System</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">An Avorix chef comes to your operation and documents your menu. Every dish is broken down into simple steps, with photos, precise quantities, and timing. Everything goes into the Cook App.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">2 &middot; The Training</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Your team is trained right at the stove, by a chef with at least sous chef experience. Until every team member can cook every dish independently.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">3 &middot; The Reinforcement</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">When you're short on staff, we provide them. Avorix employs permanent chefs that we lease to you legally. With an official staff leasing permit.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mt-6">Your guests notice nothing. They experience your kitchen and your recipes — just reliably at the same quality.</p>
      <div class="mt-6">
        <a href="/en/contact" data-cta-location="restaurants-system" class="border-2 border-brand-500 text-brand-500 px-6 py-3 rounded-xl font-bold hover:bg-brand-50 transition-colors inline-block">How the Avorix System Works</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Fixed Menu -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">A Fixed Menu Is Secured Faster Than You Think.</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">A typical inn has 12 dishes on the menu. That takes one documentation block and one training block. No months-long projects, no renovations, no effort on your part.</p>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
        <p class="text-neutral-600"><strong class="text-neutral-900">Example:</strong> 12 dishes, one on-site documentation block, one training block at the stove. After that, your team works independently with the app.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Four Steps -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-neutral-50 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-8">Four Steps, a Few Weeks.</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-brand-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold shrink-0">1</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900">Conversation</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-1">30 minutes, via video or on-site. You tell us where things get stuck. We honestly say whether Avorix fits you.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-brand-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold shrink-0">2</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900">Documentation</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-1">An Avorix chef comes to you, cooks with your team, and documents every dish on your menu in the app.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-brand-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold shrink-0">3</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900">Training</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-1">Your team learns the system right at the stove. Guided by a chef with at least sous chef experience.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-brand-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold shrink-0">4</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900">Independent</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-1">The app guides your team through every day. New dishes are added by you or by us. We stay reachable.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pilot -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">As a Pilot Operation at Half the Price.</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">We're looking for operations that will be the first to use our system and give us honest feedback. In return, pilot operations receive significantly reduced rates in 2026.</p>
      <a href="/en/pilot-program" data-cta-location="restaurants-pilot" class="border-2 border-brand-500 text-brand-500 px-6 py-3 rounded-xl font-bold hover:bg-brand-50 transition-colors inline-block">To the Pilot Program</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-neutral-50 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <details open class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4">
          <summary class="font-bold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer">We change the menu seasonally. Does that work?</summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-3">Yes. New dishes are added by you or by us. Proven dishes stay in your Recipe Library and can be recalled instantly.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4">
          <summary class="font-bold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer">We're a family business and not very tech-savvy. Will it still work?</summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-3">Yes, that's exactly what the app is built for. If you can look at a photo and check a box, you can work with it. Training happens at the stove, not at a computer.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4">
          <summary class="font-bold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer">What does our chef think of this?</summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-3">A good chef gets better with Avorix, not replaced. Their knowledge is finally captured, their team works more independently, and they can focus on what they do best.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4">
          <summary class="font-bold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer">Can we afford this?</summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-3">The question is whether you can afford not to. A missing chef costs you revenue, quality, and reputation. In the first conversation, we'll transparently calculate what Avorix costs and what it saves.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final CTA -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Secure Your House's Knowledge. While It's Still in the House.</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">30 minutes, free, no obligation. Tell us about your kitchen, and we'll honestly say whether Avorix fits you.</p>
      <a href="/en/contact" data-cta-location="restaurants-final" class="bg-brand-500 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-xl font-bold text-lg hover:bg-brand-600 transition-colors inline-block">Book a Demo</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
